<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "https://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
  LorvexCarPlay.entitlements
  PROVISIONING REQUIRED: These entitlements activate the CarPlay template
  application scene. Apple must approve each entitlement key for the Lorvex
  App ID before this file has any effect at runtime.

  Steps to activate:
    1. Submit a CarPlay entitlement request at
       developer.apple.com → Certificates, Identifiers & Profiles → your
       App ID → Additional Capabilities → CarPlay.
    2. Once approved, merge these keys into LorvexMobileApp.entitlements, OR
       set this file as the Code Signing Entitlements for the iOS app target
       in Xcode / XcodeGen.
    3. Rebuild and re-profile the app.

  Category choice: com.apple.developer.carplay-communication is the correct
  category for a productivity / to-do / scheduling app. The previous file
  declared both carplay-maps AND carplay-general, which are mutually exclusive
  categories — Apple's portal enforces one category per App ID.
  carplay-maps is for navigation apps; carplay-general is an internal Apple
  category unavailable to third parties.

  Until Apple grants the entitlement the CarPlay scene configuration in
  Info.plist is silently ignored. The code compiles and tests pass without it.
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
  <!-- Communication category: correct for task management / scheduling apps. -->
  <key>com.apple.developer.carplay-communication</key>
  <true/>
</dict>
</plist>
